## 7. Risk Assessment

### 7.1 PRD Risks with Technical Mitigations

| ID | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Technical Mitigation |
|----|------|------------|--------|---------------------|
| R1 | Drag-and-drop complexity with HTML5 API | Medium | High | Implement fallback to @dnd-kit library if HTML5 DnD proves insufficient; create abstraction layer in useDragDrop hook |
| R2 | Fractional indexing precision limits | Low | Medium | Implement automatic position rebalancing when diff < 0.001; use FLOAT for positions with sufficient precision |
| R3 | AG Grid learning curve | Medium | Low | Follow official AG Grid React documentation; start with basic configuration, add features incrementally |
| R4 | Docker networking issues on different platforms | Medium | Medium | Test on Linux, macOS, Windows during development; document known issues and workarounds; use standard Docker networking |
| R5 | Test coverage targets not met | Medium | Medium | Write tests alongside implementation (TDD approach); use Jest coverage reports for tracking; create dedicated testing phase |

### 7.2 Technical Risks

| ID | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|----|------|------------|--------|------------|
| TR1 | Database connection pool exhaustion | Low | High | Configure appropriate pool size (10-20 connections); implement connection timeout; add health checks |
| TR2 | Frontend state synchronization issues | Medium | Medium | Implement optimistic updates with rollback; use single source of truth pattern; add error boundaries |
| TR3 | CORS misconfiguration blocking requests | Low | High | Test CORS configuration early in development; document allowed origins; add CORS debugging middleware |
| TR4 | AG Grid bundle size impact | Low | Medium | Use AG Grid Community (smaller than Enterprise); implement code splitting for reports route |
| TR5 | Position rebalance transaction failures | Low | Medium | Wrap rebalance in database transaction; add retry logic; implement position validation |

